The paper deals with a problem of distributed coverage of a network by mobile agents, which involves coordination and optimization. This suggests that the paper may belong to the Multi-Agent Systems (cs.MA) category. Additionally, the paper involves graph theory and optimization, which are relevant to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) and Systems and Control (cs.SY) categories. The use of mobile agents and optimization techniques also suggests that the paper may belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) category. Finally, the paper formulates the problem in a game-theoretic setting, which is relevant to the Game Theory (cs.GT) category.
